features: SILICONE BABY PACIFIER. Soothe baby with lightweight and soft 100% silicone pacifier. BPA-free, one-piece construction designed for babies 0-6 months.

CONTOURED COMFORTABLE SHIELD. The one-piece construction of the HappyPaci features a contoured butterfly-shaped shield for comfort. The shield curves away from baby’s face, providing plenty of room for little noses and cheeks.
EASY TRANSITION TO PACIFIER. The unique 100% silicone HappyPaci design features the same shape as the Dr. Brown’s bottle nipple that’s familiar to baby.
DURABLE AND EASY TO CLEAN. The one-piece construction makes the silicone pacifier ideal for simplified cleaning. Dishwasher (top rack) and sterilizer safe.
3-PACK NEWBORN BABY PACIFIER. Adorable and aesthetically coordinated 3-pack baby pacifier with a variety of colors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple Easy to Clean Design
reviews.reviewText: Inexpensive, durable, super easy to clean, connects to leashes pretty well, easy to hold for baby or momma. Love the simple design. My first baby absolutely loved this specific binky. Not going to expect the next one to love it necessarily, but will definitely try!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My babies favorite!
reviews.reviewText: My baby can not get enough of this pacifier. It matches very well to the nipple type of dr browns bottles. I breastfeed, bottle feed, and this pacifier has been able to compare to all of that. Very easy to clean. Durable and last forever. I think I have at least 10 of these exact pacifiers. Not because they don’t last, but you know pacifiers are always falling or getting lost. My baby loves them so much I know I need a back up at all times.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great! But for older babies!
reviews.reviewText: My babe loves these pacifiers! We use the Dr.Brown narrow bottles and the pacifiers are the same shape which is fun! They are kind of larger, so younger babies (like my 0-1 month old) had a hard time at first. This is the only pacifier she will take now. They are also very easy to clean.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love that they are durable and easy to clean. Plus the variety of colors was just a plus.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect pacifier for babies using the Dr. Brown bottles and nipples
reviews.reviewText: We purchased everything Dr. Brown for our daughter’s baby. These little pacifiers are a game changer. Especially if you’re waiting for a bottle to warm up in the Dr. Brown’s bottle warmer and sterilization unit. They match the bottle nipple perfectly. It’s made out of soft silicone, and can be sterilized in the Dr. Brown’s bottle warmer and sterilization unit. Reasonably priced, we make sure we buy them frequently, for our home as well as our daughter’s home. Babies love and need to safely suck for comfort as well as nutrition. Dr. Brown’s pacifiers are simply the best. Our three month old grandson agrees.

reviews.reviewText: This is definitely worth it. My son loves this item and it’s durable and easy to clean. It’s easy for him to hold and it definitely helps with teething especially if you put it in the freezer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Dr. Brown's HappyPaci 100% Silicone Pacifiers have become an essential comfort for my 15-month-old son. Their soft and flexible design makes them his absolute favorite, providing a soothing experience. To ensure we're always prepared, I keep at least a dozen of these pacifiers both at home and in my car. The convenient three-pack in white, blue, and light blue colors allows for a handy rotation, ensuring there's always a clean and comforting pacifier within arm's reach. I particularly appreciate that they are BPA-free, prioritizing my son's safety while offering a reliable solution to keep him content and happy.
One piece soother is pastel Colors. Very soft nipples. Super light weight. Came in two separate packing with 3 each in one. Great for gifting too.

The only type of pacifier my son will use, absolutely so grateful for these! And the price isn't bad (we have lost a bunch so I've had to restock, I like to have 3-4 in his crib at night and they do move around, so it's great they're well priced to have extras on hand).

reviews.reviewTitle: Seems big at first but works - my baby's fave!
reviews.reviewText: Edit: My 5 month old loves these soothers because they are easy to hold, especially at night when my baby is looking for a soother to suck on. They are also easy to attach to any pacifier clip which makes it handy in the carseat or stroller. I purchased another pack.These soothers seemed large compared to several other brands my 4 month old uses, but it's fine. The thickness seems to make it durable and I do like the flat "butterfly" shape that doesn't trap drool around my baby's lips. I purchased these soothers because my baby has been using Dr. Brown's bottles. They sterilize fine in a brezza sterlizer/dryer so I'm happy with the purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on May 29, 2022
reviews.reviewText: My son loved chewing on the dr brown bottles and won’t take a dummy anymore so thought I would try these as same shape as the tray on the bottle. But they are to big and he can’t keep it in his mouth he is 7 months old
The product is nicely packed and very comfortable for baby
